# Comment Support Matrix

| DB         | `--`        | `# `   | `/**/`  | Notes |
|------------|-------------|--------|---------|-------|
| Oracle     | YES         | NO     | YES     | `--` is standard |
| MySQL      | `-- ` only* | YES    | YES     | `--` MUST have trailing space/newline |
| PostgreSQL | YES         | NO     | YES     | `--` is standard |
| MSSQL      | YES         | NO     | YES     | both work |

*MySQL: `--comment` (no space) is treated as a subtraction operator. Must be `-- comment` with at least one whitespace char.

# Pro tips
- If `--` gets URL-decoded weirdly, try `--+` (the `+` becomes a space when URL decoded)
- If the trailing comment is stripped by a WAF, use `/**/` and put a `-- -` at the end too
- For URL params, encode the `#` as `%23` (otherwise the browser treats it as a fragment)
- For inline comments inside a payload (e.g. bypass keyword filtering): `UN/**/ION SE/**/LECT` works on MySQL
